-- US Airways Said to Hire Advisers for Possible AMR Bid
-- B y   M a r y   S c h l a n g e n s t e i n
-- 2012-01-12T21:05:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/us-airways-said-to-hire-advisers-for-possible-amr-bid.html
US Airways Group Inc. (LCC)  has hired
financial advisers to assess a possible bid for American
Airlines parent AMR Corp. in bankruptcy, a person with knowledge
of the matter said.  No decisions about an offer have been made, said the
person, who asked not to be identified because the deliberations
aren’t public. Todd Lehmacher, an airline spokesman, said  US
Airways  doesn’t comment on speculation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mary Schlangenstein in Dallas at 
